Materials and methods: In this study, we analyzed datasets sourced from the Gene Expression Omnibus (GEO) database, and identified shared genes of IBD and psoriasis through differential expression analysis and weighted gene co-expression network analysis (WGCNA).

In this study, we first screened IBD and psoriasis datasets from GEO, conducted differential gene expression analysis and WGCNA, and identified AQP9 as a shared diagnostic gene using three machine learning methods.

Since our last report in 2019, we have continued to acquire these classical types of expression data; developed a searchable index of RNA-Seq and microarray experiments that allows users to quickly and reliably find specific mouse expression studies in ArrayExpress ( https://www.ebi.ac.uk/arrayexpress/ ) and GEO ( https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/geo/ ); and expanded GXD to include RNA-Seq data.
